  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "What is الاسم المنقوص?",
      "titleArabic": "تعريف الاسم المنقوص",
      "content": [
        "الاسم المنقوص is a noun ending in ya (ي) preceded by kasra, like القَاضِي (the judge) and الدَّاعِي (the caller).",
        "In the nominative and genitive cases, the ya takes an estimated vowel. In the accusative, it takes a visible fatha."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Ends in ي preceded by kasra (ـِي)",
        "Common examples: القَاضِي، الرَّامِي، الدَّاعِي، الْهَادِي",
        "Nominative: estimated damma (الْقَاضِي)",
        "Genitive: estimated kasra (الْقَاضِي)",
        "Accusative: visible fatha (الْقَاضِيَ)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ الْقَاضِي", "english": "The judge came (nom. estimated)" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ الْقَاضِيَ", "english": "I saw the judge (acc. visible fatha)" },
        { "arabic": "سَلَّمْتُ عَلَى الْقَاضِي", "english": "I greeted the judge (gen. estimated)" },
        { "arabic": "الدَّاعِي إِلَى الْخَيْرِ", "english": "The caller to goodness" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Tanween with المنقوص",
      "titleArabic": "التنوين مع الاسم المنقوص",
      "content": [
        "When the noun is indefinite (with tanween), the ya is dropped in the nominative and genitive, but kept in the accusative.",
        "We say قَاضٍ (a judge) in nominative/genitive, but قَاضِيًا in accusative."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Nominative indefinite: قَاضٍ (ya dropped, tanween kasra)",
        "Genitive indefinite: قَاضٍ (ya dropped, tanween kasra)",
        "Accusative indefinite: قَاضِيًا (ya kept, tanween fatha)",
        "The tanween replaces the dropped ya in nom/gen"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ قَاضٍ عَادِلٌ", "english": "A just judge came" },
        { "arabic": "مَرَرْتُ بِقَاضٍ", "english": "I passed by a judge" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ قَاضِيًا", "english": "I saw a judge" },
        { "arabic": "هُوَ رَاعٍ لِلْغَنَمِ", "english": "He is a shepherd of sheep" }
      ]
    }
  ],
